@node Overview
@chapter Overview

The @samp{wikipedia.el} package provides a comprehensive Emacs interface for Wikipedia. @*
It builds on top of @samp{mediawiki.el}, which handles the low-level protocol details, @*
and adds higher-level workflows for editing, reviewing, and managing Wikipedia @*
content. @*

The package requires Emacs 29.1 or later and @samp{mediawiki.el} for the @*
underlying API communication.  Optionally, @samp{pangram.el} can be @*
installed for AI-generated text detection; when available, an ``AI @*
Detection'' group appears in the transient menu (@ref{Transient menu}). @*
Before using any commands, you must configure at least one @*
wiki site via @samp{mediawiki-site-alist} and establish a session with @*
@code{wikipedia-login} (@ref{Session management}). @*

The package is organized around several core workflows: @*

@itemize
@item
@strong{Page editing}: open pages for editing in @samp{mediawiki-mode} buffers, @*
preview rendered HTML, and publish changes back to the wiki @*
(@ref{Page editing}). @*

@item
@strong{Draft management}: save work-in-progress edits as local files that @*
persist across sessions (@ref{Draft management}). @*

@item
@strong{Watchlist}: browse your watchlist with a grouped, expandable @*
interface that shows recent changes organized by page, with unread @*
tracking and background prefetching of diffs @*
(@ref{Watchlist}). @*

@item
@strong{Revision history}: inspect the full revision history of any page, @*
view diffs between arbitrary revisions, and navigate between @*
historical snapshots (@ref{Revision history}). @*

@item
@strong{User inspection}: view user contributions, visit user pages, send @*
thanks, and look up detailed editing statistics via XTools @*
(@ref{User inspection}, @ref{XTools statistics}). @*

@item
@strong{Local mirror}: synchronize watched pages to a local SQLite database @*
for offline browsing and faster access (@ref{Synchronization and local mirror}). @*

@item
@strong{Diff follow mode}: automatically display diffs as you navigate @*
entries in the watchlist, history, or contributions buffers @*
(@ref{Diff follow mode}). @*

@item
@strong{AI review}: use an LLM to score watchlist changes by review @*
priority, so you can focus on the edits that matter most @*
(@ref{AI review}). @*
@end itemize

All commands are accessible through a unified transient menu @*
(@ref{Transient menu}). @*

