@node Diff display
@section Diff display

@vindex wikipedia-diff-function
The user option @code{wikipedia-diff-function} controls how diffs are @*
displayed throughout the package.  It accepts two values: @*

@itemize
@item
@code{unified} (the default): show diffs in a single buffer using Emacs's @*
built-in @code{diff-mode}.  This is compact and integrates well with the @*
diff follow mode (@ref{Diff follow mode}). @*

@item
@code{ediff}: use @code{ediff-buffers} for side-by-side comparison.  This gives @*
a richer interactive experience but opens multiple windows and is @*
incompatible with diff follow mode. @*
@end itemize

Change this option if you prefer side-by-side comparison and do not use @*
diff follow mode. @*

@node Draft storage
@section Draft storage

@vindex wikipedia-draft-directory
The user option @code{wikipedia-draft-directory} specifies the directory @*
where local drafts are stored.  Each draft is saved as a @samp{.wiki} file @*
named after the page title, using a byte-level encoding scheme for @*
filesystem safety.  The default value is @samp{wikipedia-drafts/} inside @*
@code{user-emacs-directory}. @*

Change this if you want drafts stored in a different location, for @*
example a directory that is synchronized across machines. @*

@node XTools integration
@section XTools integration

@vindex wikipedia-xtools-base-url
@vindex wikipedia-xtools-project
The user option @code{wikipedia-xtools-base-url} specifies the base URL for @*
the XTools API@.  The default value is @samp{https://xtools.wmcloud.org/api}. @*
You would only change this if the XTools service moves to a different @*
URL@. @*

The user option @code{wikipedia-xtools-project} specifies the default project @*
for XTools queries.  The default value is @samp{en.wikipedia.org}.  Change @*
this if you primarily edit a different Wikipedia language edition or @*
another MediaWiki project (e.g., @samp{de.wikipedia.org} or @*
@samp{commons.wikimedia.org}). @*

@node Local database
@section Local database

@vindex wikipedia-db-file
The user option @code{wikipedia-db-file} specifies the path to the SQLite @*
database file used for local page storage.  The default value is @*
@samp{wikipedia.db} inside @code{user-emacs-directory}.  Change this if you want @*
the database stored elsewhere, for example to keep it separate from @*
your Emacs configuration. @*

@node Synchronization
@section Synchronization

@vindex wikipedia-sync-revision-limit
@vindex wikipedia-sync-fetch-content
The user option @code{wikipedia-sync-revision-limit} controls the maximum @*
number of revisions to synchronize per page.  The default value is 20. @*
Increase this if you want deeper local history; decrease it if @*
synchronization is too slow. @*

The user option @code{wikipedia-sync-fetch-content} controls whether full @*
revision content (wikitext) is fetched during synchronization.  When @*
non-nil (the default), the content of the most recent revision is @*
downloaded and stored locally, enabling offline viewing and local diffs. @*
Set this to @code{nil} if you only want revision metadata without the actual @*
page content. @*

@node AI review options
@section AI review options

These options require the @samp{gptel} package.

@menu
* Review prompt::
* Review model::
* Automatic scoring::
@end menu

@node Review prompt
@subsection Review prompt

@vindex wikipedia-ai-review-system-prompt
@vindex wikipedia-ai-review-prompt
The user option @code{wikipedia-ai-review-system-prompt} is the system @*
prompt sent to the LLM.  It instructs the model to return a JSON object @*
with a @samp{score} (0.0--1.0) and a @samp{reason}.  You should not normally @*
need to change this. @*

The user option @code{wikipedia-ai-review-prompt} describes which edits @*
to flag.  The default asks the model to identify substantive changes @*
(adding or removing sentences, changing factual claims, altering @*
structure) and ignore minor edits like typo fixes or formatting.  @*
Customize this to match your review priorities. @*

@node Review model
@subsection Review model

@vindex wikipedia-ai-review-model
@vindex wikipedia-ai-review-backend
The user option @code{wikipedia-ai-review-model} specifies the LLM model @*
to use for scoring.  When nil (the default), the current @*
@code{gptel-model} is used.  Set this to a specific model symbol to use @*
a different model for review than for other @samp{gptel} tasks. @*

The user option @code{wikipedia-ai-review-backend} specifies the @*
@samp{gptel} backend name (e.g., @samp{"Gemini"} or @samp{"Claude"}).  When nil @*
(the default), the backend is inferred from @*
@code{wikipedia-ai-review-model}, falling back to @code{gptel-backend}. @*

@node Automatic scoring
@subsection Automatic scoring

@vindex wikipedia-ai-review-auto
@vindex wikipedia-watchlist-score-reason-auto
The user option @code{wikipedia-ai-review-auto}, when non-nil, @*
automatically runs AI scoring after each watchlist refresh.  This @*
eliminates the need to press @samp{R} manually. @*

The user option @code{wikipedia-watchlist-score-reason-auto}, when @*
non-nil, automatically displays the AI score and reason in the echo @*
area as you move between watchlist entries. @*

