@node Navigation
@subsection Navigation

@findex wikipedia-watchlist-toggle-expand
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-expand-all
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-collapse-all
Group headers with more than one change can be expanded and collapsed. @*
The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-toggle-expand}, bound to @samp{TAB} and @*
@samp{SPC}, toggles the group at point.  Expanded groups show individual @*
entries indented below the header, with per-edit timestamps, users, size @*
changes, and summaries.  The indicators @samp{▶} (collapsed) and @samp{▼} @*
(expanded) show the current state. @*

The commands @code{wikipedia-watchlist-expand-all} (@samp{e}) and @*
@code{wikipedia-watchlist-collapse-all} (@samp{c}) expand or collapse every group @*
at once. @*

@node Actions
@subsection Actions

@findex wikipedia-watchlist-open-page
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-show-diff
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-show-history
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-browse
The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-open-page} (@samp{RET}, @samp{o}) opens the page @*
at point for editing, marking it as read.  The command @*
@code{wikipedia-watchlist-show-diff} (@samp{d}, @samp{v}) displays the diff for the @*
change at point, using the method specified by @code{wikipedia-diff-function} @*
(@ref{Diff display}).  The command @*
@code{wikipedia-watchlist-show-history} (@samp{h}) opens the full revision history @*
for the page.  The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-browse} (@samp{b}) opens the @*
page in an external browser. @*

@node Unread tracking
@subsection Unread tracking

@findex wikipedia-watchlist-mark-all-read
Unread entries are displayed in bold (using the @code{wikipedia-watchlist-unread} @*
face).  Opening a page or viewing its diff marks it as read, both @*
locally and on the server.  The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-mark-all-read} @*
(@samp{m} or @samp{!}) marks every entry as read. @*

@node Managing watched pages
@subsection Managing watched pages

@findex wikipedia-watchlist-watch
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-unwatch
The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-watch} (@samp{w}) adds a page to your @*
watchlist.  The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-unwatch} (@samp{x}) removes a @*
page, after confirmation.  Both commands default to the title at point @*
and send the request asynchronously. @*

