@node Revision history
@section Revision history

@findex wikipedia-history
@findex wikipedia-history-refresh
The command @code{wikipedia-history} opens a buffer displaying the revision @*
history of a page.  When called interactively, it prompts for the page @*
title.  The history buffer shows each revision's ID, date, author, @*
size, and edit summary in a tabulated list, sorted by date (newest @*
first). @*

@menu
* Viewing and comparing revisions::
* Full keybinding reference: Full keybinding reference (1). 
@end menu

@node Viewing and comparing revisions
@subsection Viewing and comparing revisions

@findex wikipedia-history-view-revision
@findex wikipedia-history-diff-to-previous
@findex wikipedia-history-diff-to-current
@findex wikipedia-history-diff-revisions
@findex wikipedia-history-browse-revision
The command @code{wikipedia-history-view-revision} (@samp{RET}, @samp{v}) fetches and @*
displays the full wikitext of the revision at point in a read-only @*
buffer. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-history-diff-to-previous} (@samp{d}) shows the diff @*
between the revision at point and its parent revision.  This corresponds @*
to Wikipedia's ``prev'' link.  The command @*
@code{wikipedia-history-diff-to-current} (@samp{c}) shows the diff between the @*
revision at point and the most recent revision, corresponding to @*
Wikipedia's ``cur'' link. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-history-diff-revisions} (@samp{D}) prompts for two @*
revision IDs and displays the diff between them.  This is useful for @*
comparing non-adjacent revisions. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-history-browse-revision} (@samp{b}) opens the revision @*
at point in an external browser. @*

