@node Contribution actions
@subsection Contribution actions

@findex wikipedia-user-contributions-view-diff
@findex wikipedia-user-contributions-view-revision
@findex wikipedia-user-contributions-open-page
@findex wikipedia-user-contributions-browse
@findex wikipedia-user-contributions-show-history
@findex wikipedia-user-contributions-thank
The command @code{wikipedia-user-contributions-view-diff} (@samp{RET}, @samp{d}) shows @*
the diff between the contribution at point and its parent revision.  The @*
command @code{wikipedia-user-contributions-view-revision} (@samp{v}) displays the @*
full wikitext.  The command @code{wikipedia-user-contributions-open-page} @*
(@samp{o}) opens the page for editing. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-user-contributions-browse} (@samp{b}) opens the @*
revision in an external browser.  The command @*
@code{wikipedia-user-contributions-show-history} (@samp{h}) opens the full page @*
history.  The command @code{wikipedia-user-contributions-thank} (@samp{t}) sends a @*
thank notification for the edit. @*

@node User page and profile commands
@subsection User page and profile commands

@findex wikipedia-user-page
@findex wikipedia-user-talk
@findex wikipedia-user-browse
@findex wikipedia-user-at-point
@findex wikipedia-user-stats
The command @code{wikipedia-user-page} opens the user page (@samp{User:USERNAME}) @*
for editing.  The command @code{wikipedia-user-talk} opens the user's talk @*
page.  The command @code{wikipedia-user-browse} opens the user page in an @*
external browser. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-user-at-point} inspects the user at point in any @*
of the list buffers (watchlist, history, contributions), opening their @*
contributions. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-user-stats} is a convenience wrapper that calls @*
@code{wikipedia-xtools-user-stats} (@ref{XTools statistics}). @*

@node Sending thanks
@subsection Sending thanks

@findex wikipedia-thank
The command @code{wikipedia-thank} sends a thank notification to the author @*
of the revision at point.  It prompts for confirmation before sending. @*
This command works from any buffer where a revision ID is available @*
(history, watchlist, or contributions). @*

