@node Database management
@subsection Database management

@findex wikipedia-db-close
@findex wikipedia-db-stats
The command @code{wikipedia-db-close} closes the database connection.  The @*
connection is opened lazily on first use and remains open for the @*
duration of the Emacs session. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-db-stats} displays a summary of the database @*
contents: the number of pages, watched pages, revisions, and revisions @*
with stored content. @*

@node Diff follow mode
@section Diff follow mode

@findex wikipedia-diff-follow-mode
The minor mode @code{wikipedia-diff-follow-mode} automatically displays the @*
diff for the entry at point whenever you move to a different line in a @*
list buffer.  It works in the watchlist, history, and contributions @*
buffers and is toggled with @samp{f} in any of these modes. @*

When enabled, navigating to a new entry triggers an automatic diff @*
display in an adjacent window.  If both revisions are already in the @*
cache (populated by the watchlist's background prefetching), the diff @*
appears instantly.  Otherwise, the revisions are fetched asynchronously @*
and the diff is displayed when both arrive, with a ``Loading diff@dots{}'' @*
placeholder in the meantime. @*

Diff follow mode requires @code{wikipedia-diff-function} to be set to @*
@code{unified} (@ref{Diff display}).  Attempting @*
to enable it when @code{ediff} is selected produces a warning and the mode @*
remains disabled. @*

In watchlist mode, viewing a diff via follow mode also marks the entry @*
as read (@ref{Unread tracking}). @*

@node AI review
@section AI review

@findex wikipedia-ai-review-watchlist
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-sort-by-score
@findex wikipedia-watchlist-show-score-reason
The command @code{wikipedia-ai-review-watchlist} (@samp{R} in the watchlist) @*
scores each watchlist group using an LLM@.  For each group, it computes @*
a unified diff between the oldest base revision and the newest @*
revision, sends it to the model with the configured prompt @*
(@ref{Review prompt}), and stores the returned score (0.0--1.0) and @*
reason.  Scores appear in the watchlist's @samp{Score} column and are @*
persisted in the local SQLite database. @*

Processing is asynchronous and sequential: each group is scored one at @*
a time.  Progress is reported in the echo area.  Re-invoking @samp{R} @*
while a review is running cancels the previous run and starts a fresh @*
one. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-sort-by-score} (@samp{S}) sorts @*
the watchlist by score, highest first.  Unscored entries are placed at @*
the bottom. @*

The command @code{wikipedia-watchlist-show-score-reason} (@samp{I}) @*
displays the AI's reasoning for the score of the entry at point in the @*
echo area. @*

High scores (>= 0.7) are highlighted with the @*
@code{wikipedia-watchlist-score-high} face, and low scores (<= 0.3) use @*
the @code{wikipedia-watchlist-score-low} face. @*

@node Transient menu
@section Transient menu

@findex wikipedia-transient
The command @code{wikipedia-transient} opens a transient menu providing quick @*
access to all @samp{wikipedia.el} commands.  The menu is organized into @*
groups: @*

@itemize
@item
@strong{Page}: open, publish, preview, browse, and login. @*
@item
@strong{Draft}: save, open, and delete drafts. @*
@item
@strong{Watchlist}: open the watchlist, watch/unwatch pages, browse, and mark @*
all read. @*
@item
@strong{History}: open page history. @*
@item
@strong{User}: user contributions, user page, user talk, browse user, and @*
thank. @*
@item
@strong{XTools}: user stats, page stats, and top editors. @*
@item
@strong{Sync & Mirror}: sync page, sync watchlist, sync update, and mirror @*
browser. @*
@item
@strong{AI Detection} (requires @samp{pangram.el}): detect AI-generated text and @*
clear overlays.  This group is only shown when @samp{pangram.el} is @*
installed. @*

@item
@strong{AI Editing} (requires @samp{gptel}): generate citations and review @*
watchlist changes with AI@.  This group is only shown when @samp{gptel} @*
is installed. @*
@end itemize

Bind @code{wikipedia-transient} to a convenient key for quick access to any @*
command in the package. @*

